001package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.util;
002
003/**
004 * Represents a function that accepts two input arguments and produces a result.
005 *
006 * <p>This functional interface is similar to {@link java.util.function.BiFunction}, allowing
007 * the execution of a function that processes two inputs and returns a computed value.
008 *
009 * <p>The first input argument, {@code T}, represents the primary entity being processed.
010 * The second input argument, {@code U}, provides additional data or context necessary for computation.
011 * The function returns a result of type {@code V}, which represents the computed output.
012 *
013 * <p>This interface is commonly used for defining behavior dynamically, such as handling
014 * exceptions in Selenium WebDriver operations, as seen in {@code ExceptionHandlingWebDriver}.
015 *
016 * @author Cyborg Code Syndicate üíçüë®üíª
017 */
018@FunctionalInterface
019public interface BiFunction<T, U, V> {
020
021   /**
022    * Applies this function to the given arguments and produces a result.
023    *
024    * @param t The first input argument.
025    * @param u The second input argument.
026    * @return The computed result of type {@code V}.
027    */
028   V apply(T t, U u);
029}
